      <div class=3D"product__content">
        <h3 id=3D"faqs"><a href=3D"https://once.com/campfire#faqs">Frequent=
ly asked questions</a></h3>
        <h4 id=3D"once-really"><a href=3D"https://once.com/campfire#once-re=
ally">Just $299, once, really? No per-user fees?</a></h4>
        <p>Yes, Campfire is just $299, once. No ongoing fees, no monthly fe=
es, no annual fees, no per-user fees, no support contracts, nothing. You do=
n=E2=80=99t rent Campfire like SaaS products =E2=80=94 you buy it, it=E2=80=
=99s yours. Like a jar of peanut butter.</p>
        <h4 id=3D"buy-or-download"><a href=3D"https://once.com/campfire#buy=
-or-download">Does each user have to buy or download it?</a></h4>
        <p>Nope =E2=80=94 one person (you, your IT person, etc.) buys it, d=
ownloads it, and installs it on a server you control. It could be a remote =
shared server, too. Either way, once it=E2=80=99s installed and running, ju=
st invite co-workers to the system and they log into it via the web or thei=
r mobile devices like any group app.</p>
        <h4 id=3D"updates"><a href=3D"https://once.com/campfire#updates">Ho=
w do updates work? Do they cost extra?</a></h4>
        <p>Each Campfire installation pings our server once a day to see if=
 there are any updates. If so, it=E2=80=99ll download and automatically ins=
tall them. You can turn this off if you=E2=80=99d prefer to do it manually.=
 As far as cost goes, if it=E2=80=99s on the same root version you have =E2=
=80=94 like from 1.0 to 1.1 =E2=80=94 the update will be free. Jumping vers=
ion numbers (from 1.x to 2.x, for example), may cost extra. It=E2=80=99ll b=
e up to you if you want to jump versions.</p>
        <h4 id=3D"mobile-apps"><a href=3D"https://once.com/campfire#mobile-=
apps">Are native iOS and Android apps available?</a></h4>
        <p>Campfire is designed to work beautifully on the mobile web =E2=
=80=94 either as a tab in your mobile browser, or as a PWA (Progressive Web=
 App) which you can launch right from your mobile device=E2=80=99s home scr=
een like all your other apps. And like native apps, you=E2=80=99ll get badg=
es on your icon and push notifications if you=E2=80=99d like.</p>
        <h4 id=3D"support"><a href=3D"https://once.com/campfire#support">Is=
 customer support included?</a></h4>
        <p>Bare bones support is included, yes. That means we=E2=80=99re ha=
ppy to occasionally help with the basics, but we can=E2=80=99t troubleshoot=
 complex custom installations, or fix stuff you broke when you changed the =
code. Please send feature requests to <a href=3D"mailto:email@once.com">ema=
il@once.com</a>.</p>
        <h4 id=3D"multiple-places"><a href=3D"https://once.com/campfire#mul=
tiple-places">Can we buy one copy of Campfire and run it in multiple places=
?</a></h4>
        <p>When you buy Campfire, we=E2=80=99ll issue you a license to inst=
all it on a single domain name. If you=E2=80=99d like to install it on mult=
iple servers with different domain names, you=E2=80=99ll need to buy separa=
te copies per domain.</p>
        <h4 id=3D"white-label-or-resell"><a href=3D"https://once.com/campfi=
re#white-label-or-resell">Can we white label or resell Campfire?</a></h4>
        <p>Not currently. If interested, contact us at <a href=3D"mailto:em=
ail@once.com">email@once.com</a> and we=E2=80=99ll keep you in mind should =
we change our mind. Please be sure to review the <a href=3D"https://once.co=
m/license">license agreement</a> for further details.</p>
        <h4 id=3D"run-on-shared-server"><a href=3D"https://once.com/campfir=
e#run-on-shared-server">Can we run Campfire on a shared server like Digital=
Ocean?</a></h4>
        <p>Absolutely. Wherever you can host something like WordPress, you =
can host Campfire. Please refer to the <a href=3D"https://once.com/campfire=
#requirements">system requirements</a> section for further details.</p>
        <h4 id=3D"no-internet"><a href=3D"https://once.com/campfire#no-inte=
rnet">Can we run Campfire where we don=E2=80=99t have the internet?</a></h4=
>
        <p>Yes! Since Campfire runs on your own server, and doesn=E2=80=99t=
 ping back to a remote server elsewhere, Campfire can run on air gapped net=
works without access to the outside internet. This means it=E2=80=99s an ex=
cellent fit in research facilities or other high security environments. Try=
 that with remotely hosted SaaS products (Hint: you can=E2=80=99t).</p>
        <h4 id=3D"import-from"><a href=3D"https://once.com/campfire#import-=
from">Can we import our Slack or Teams data into Campfire?</a></h4>
        <p>Not at this time. Campfire is a fresh start.</p>
